refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.returnvalues;


 Returns the previously defined exception handler, or &null; on error. If
 no previous handler was defined, &null; is also returned.

  &reftitle.examples;



    set_exception_handler example


<?php
function exception_handler(Throwable $exception) {
  echo "Uncaught exception: " , $exception->getMessage(), "\n";
}

set_exception_handler('exception_handler');

throw new Exception('Uncaught Exception');
echo "Not Executed\n";
?>

&reftitle.changelog;







     &Version;
     &Description;





     8.4.0

      Calling set_exception_handler or
      restore_exception_handler from within a
      user-defined exception handler may not immediately modify the
      active handler, as the handler is temporarily replaced internally
      to prevent recursion.
